---
import BaseLayout from '../layouts/BaseLayout.astro';
---
<BaseLayout
  title="Advertising Policy — inbrowser.sh"
  description="How inbrowser.sh handles advertising, sponsored placements and ad disclosure."
  path="/advertising"
>
  <article class="max-w-3xl mx-auto px-4 pt-10 pb-16 prose-tool">
    <h1 class="text-3xl font-semibold tracking-tight">Advertising Policy</h1>
    <p>
      inbrowser.sh is preparing to use privacy-conscious advertising to support hosting and maintenance.
      Tool functionality remains free, and ads must not block access to inputs, outputs, examples, or help content.
    </p>

    <h2>Ad placement principles</h2>
    <ul>
      <li>Ads should be clearly separated from tool controls and output panels.</li>
      <li>Ads should not imitate buttons, system messages, download controls, or copy actions.</li>
      <li>Ads should not ask users to click, refresh, or interact with them.</li>
      <li>No ad placement should appear on intentionally empty, broken, or under-construction pages.</li>
    </ul>

    <h2>Sponsored content</h2>
    <p>
      If inbrowser.sh ever publishes sponsored content, it will be clearly labeled as sponsored or advertising.
      Sponsored content will not change tool results.
    </p>

    <h2>Privacy</h2>
    <p>
      Advertising and analytics may use their own network requests and identifiers according to their
      providers' policies. inbrowser.sh tools are still designed so your pasted input and generated output remain
      in the browser.
    </p>
  </article>
</BaseLayout>
